    "Many studies have been conducted to investigate strategies to reduce the energy consumption and carbon footprint of AI models and systems [16].",
    "The research community has begun to translate this knowledge into reusable design decisions, such as architectural tactics [35].",
    "Another example is the study by Yarally et al. [36], which examined the effect of Bayesian optimization during hyperparameter tuning on the energy consumption of model training.",
    "They also investigated the complexity of AI models and concluded that the overall energy consumption of training can be halved by reducing the network complexity.",
    "Hyperparameter tuning and model complexity have increasingly become topics of interest in recent years [37,38]."
